01:15.409 --> 01:17.828
I have to record
his vital signs!

01:17.912 --> 01:19.205
No! No!

01:21.707 --> 01:22.625
Dr. Gruber?

01:22.708 --> 01:25.336
<i>Dr. Gruber, How this happened?</i>

01:30.424 --> 01:31.675
Dr. Gruber?

01:48.025 --> 01:49.819
<i>He's dead.</i>

01:49.902 --> 01:53.364
Of course, he's dead,
the dosage was too large.

01:53.447 --> 01:54.323
You killed him.

01:54.406 --> 01:56.826
No, I did not.

01:57.993 --> 02:00.621
I gave him life.

04:52.001 --> 04:54.336
All right,
I'm gonna zap her again.

04:54.420 --> 04:57.172
Charge up the paddles.

04:57.298 --> 04:58.215
Come on, let's go! Let's go!

04:58.299 --> 05:00.134
Sorry, doctor.

05:00.217 --> 05:03.178
Hold the compressions.

05:03.304 --> 05:05.139
Clear!

05:08.517 --> 05:10.978
Straight line.

05:12.563 --> 05:15.858
All right, let's call it.

05:15.941 --> 05:16.775
Cain.

05:16.859 --> 05:19.987
She just needs a little more time
for the drugs to circulate.

05:20.070 --> 05:21.697
Cain, we have done everything

05:21.780 --> 05:23.741
that can be done for this woman.

05:23.824 --> 05:25.701
She has not responded.

05:28.370 --> 05:29.913
She's gone!

05:41.258 --> 05:43.635
Cain, your optimism is touching,
but a waste of time.

05:43.719 --> 05:45.888
A good doctor
knows when to stop.

05:45.971 --> 05:46.889
- Dr. Harrod, just...
- Take her.

05:46.972 --> 05:50.100
And take her to the morgue.

05:52.770 --> 05:54.938
Gangway...

06:05.366 --> 06:06.533
Mr. Cain.

06:06.617 --> 06:07.868
Hey, Mace!

06:07.951 --> 06:09.203
I got another one for you.

06:09.286 --> 06:12.289
They ain't locked.
Doc Hill's in the autopsy room.

06:12.373 --> 06:14.541
Oh, thanks.

06:14.625 --> 06:16.752
Don't know why they keep
locked doors around here.

06:16.835 --> 06:19.254
Nobody wants in...

06:19.380 --> 06:21.006
and ain't nobody gettin' out.

06:21.090 --> 06:23.884
Yup.

06:51.620 --> 06:55.124
Full house.

07:50.095 --> 07:52.181
Oh, I'm sorry, Dan.
I didn't mean to scare you.

07:52.264 --> 07:53.348
Oh, it wasn't too bad
Dean Halsey.

07:53.474 --> 07:55.100
I just didn't know anybody was here.

07:55.184 --> 07:57.144
You mean, "anybody else".

07:57.227 --> 07:58.645
Dan, this is Herbert West.

07:58.729 --> 08:00.355
He'll be joining you
in your third year.

08:00.481 --> 08:02.316
He was doing independent
research in Switzerland

08:02.399 --> 08:04.193
with Dr. Gruber shortly before he died.

08:04.276 --> 08:06.653
Mr. West, this is Daniel Cain.

08:06.737 --> 08:08.071
(One of Miskatonic Medical's

08:08.155 --> 08:11.366
best young hopes
for the future of medicine.

08:11.492 --> 08:12.784
What were you researching?

08:12.868 --> 08:14.244
Death.

08:14.328 --> 08:17.331
Alan, we don't see you
around here much anymore.

08:17.414 --> 08:19.333
Well, I was just showing
our newest student,

08:19.416 --> 08:21.335
Herbert West here,
the not-so-grand tour.

08:21.418 --> 08:23.295
This should interest you, Carl.

08:23.378 --> 08:26.965
He worked with Hans Gruber.

08:27.049 --> 08:28.675
Mr. West?

08:28.759 --> 08:34.431
This is our eminent brain researcher
and grant machine, Dr. Carl Hill.

08:34.515 --> 08:36.517
I know your work, Dr. Hill.

08:36.558 --> 08:38.352
Quite well.

08:38.434 --> 08:40.729
Your theory on the location
of the will in the brain is...

08:40.812 --> 08:43.190
interesting...

08:43.273 --> 08:46.735
though derivative of Dr. Gruber's
research in the early '70s.

08:46.818 --> 08:50.113
So derivative, in fact, that in Europe
it's considered plagiarized.

08:50.197 --> 08:54.076
And your support of the 12-minute limit on
the life of the brain stem after death...

08:54.159 --> 08:57.079
Six to 12 minutes, Mr...

08:57.162 --> 08:59.998
West. Herbert West.

09:00.082 --> 09:03.168
Frankly, Dr. Hill?

09:03.252 --> 09:05.587
Your work on brain death
is outdated.

09:08.465 --> 09:10.801
Carl, while I remember,

09:10.884 --> 09:13.387
we're having a grant committee
meeting Thursday.

09:13.470 --> 09:16.014
Megan and I would love it
if you came to dinner.

09:16.098 --> 09:17.307
Well, I'd love to, Alan,

09:17.391 --> 09:19.393
looking forward to it.

09:19.476 --> 09:23.146
And looking forward to
seeing you in class, Mr. West.

09:39.913 --> 09:42.791
Hi.

09:45.252 --> 09:47.379
No. No.

09:48.880 --> 09:53.594
Yes! Oh, yes!

10:09.443 --> 10:12.029
Rufus!

10:12.112 --> 10:14.239
Thanks a lot, buddy.

10:14.323 --> 10:16.325
I have to go.

10:19.369 --> 10:21.204
No, stay.

10:21.288 --> 10:22.789
Daddy knows I'm here.

10:22.873 --> 10:24.625
