what Dean Halsey knows.

10:24.708 --> 10:26.793
Be reasonable.

10:26.877 --> 10:29.046
If I didn't come home
one night...

10:29.129 --> 10:30.797
just one night...

10:30.881 --> 10:32.799
What would he do?

10:32.883 --> 10:34.551
Expel me?

10:34.635 --> 10:36.803
He's out of touch with the times.

10:36.887 --> 10:38.555
That's just the way he is,

10:38.639 --> 10:41.099
the world's last living Puritan.

10:44.144 --> 10:46.146
I really hate it.

10:51.818 --> 10:53.445
The day that you graduate,

10:53.528 --> 10:57.115
the minute you get your M.D.,
I'll marry you,

10:57.199 --> 11:00.827
and I'll help you, and I'll be with you

11:00.911 --> 11:03.580
as much as I can until then.

11:03.664 --> 11:06.958
I promise.

11:07.042 --> 11:09.294
Back to square one.

11:09.378 --> 11:12.881
Well, at least it gives me
a chance to housebreak you.

11:15.133 --> 11:16.802
Housebroken, is it?

11:22.683 --> 11:25.977
I'm going to have to teach
you a lesson, my girl.

11:26.061 --> 11:28.021
What are you doing?

11:28.105 --> 11:31.858
Dan.

11:31.942 --> 11:34.986
Dan... stop, don't.

11:36.154 --> 11:37.614
Dan, stop it!

11:37.698 --> 11:38.865
Come, my pretty.

11:38.949 --> 11:41.618
Dan, I don't like that.

11:41.702 --> 11:45.872
There's not a jury in the world
that would convict me.

11:45.956 --> 11:47.624
Dan, stop it!

11:47.708 --> 11:49.626
Doctor Dan!

11:49.710 --> 11:52.879
Dan, don't, come on, stop.

11:52.963 --> 11:54.047
I really have to go.

11:54.131 --> 11:55.590
Come here! Come to me.

11:55.716 --> 11:57.718
- Oh.
- What?

11:59.761 --> 12:01.805
Oh, shit.

12:01.888 --> 12:03.056
Hi.

12:03.140 --> 12:05.559
Can I help you?

12:05.642 --> 12:07.144
You're
here about the apartment.

12:07.227 --> 12:09.604
Yes.

12:09.730 --> 12:11.815
Didn't we meet this morning?
You're...

12:11.898 --> 12:13.775
West. Herbert West.

12:13.859 --> 12:16.361
Excuse me just one sec.

12:19.531 --> 12:20.574
Come in.

12:20.657 --> 12:22.868
Thank you.

12:28.290 --> 12:29.541
I startled you.

12:29.624 --> 12:31.752
Yes, you did.

12:33.545 --> 12:37.215
May I introduce my fiancÃ©e,
Megan Halsey?

12:37.299 --> 12:40.469
- Miss Halsey.
- Mr. West.

12:40.552 --> 12:42.763
I'm afraid the place is still
kind of a mess, Mr. West.

12:42.846 --> 12:45.140
Oh... Herbert.

12:56.026 --> 12:58.695
So, you've
just come from Europe?

12:58.779 --> 13:01.198
Switzerland.

13:01.281 --> 13:03.617
What was Dr. Gruber like?
He was pretty famous.

13:03.700 --> 13:05.243
Yes, pretty famous...

13:05.327 --> 13:07.871
Does this building
have a basement?

13:12.292 --> 13:14.377
Oh, yes.

13:17.839 --> 13:20.300
Yes.

13:20.383 --> 13:23.178
I think this will be just fine.

13:23.261 --> 13:25.597
I have my things outside,
shall I move in now?

13:25.680 --> 13:28.725
Look, I have to go.

13:28.809 --> 13:30.936
I think you and Mr. West
have a lot to discuss

13:31.019 --> 13:32.354
before you decide anything.

13:32.437 --> 13:35.440
Oh, I've decided.

13:35.524 --> 13:36.733
Well, I'd like-â€”

13:36.817 --> 13:38.819
You know, you'll never even
know that I'm here.

13:38.902 --> 13:39.736
Dan, I...

13:39.820 --> 13:40.987
Except, of course,
on the first of the month.

13:41.071 --> 13:42.614
Mr. West?

13:42.697 --> 13:43.990
Miss Halsey?

13:44.074 --> 13:47.994
You didn't say why
you left Switzerland.

13:48.078 --> 13:52.082
There was no more
I could learn there.

13:55.502 --> 13:57.921
Do we... have a deal?

14:03.593 --> 14:05.011
Done.

14:06.429 --> 14:08.765
Done.

14:08.849 --> 14:13.061
You make the incision
at the base of the skull...

14:26.867 --> 14:29.536
cutting away
enough of the faschia...

14:32.581 --> 14:34.457
to get your fingers in...

14:37.711 --> 14:41.715
and then grasping firmly
with both hands,

14:41.798 --> 14:46.887
you pull the skin forward
over the head,

14:48.013 --> 14:50.974
very much like peeling
a large orange.

14:52.893 --> 14:58.440
Once the skull is plainly visible,

14:58.523 --> 15:01.651
you take the bone saw...

15:02.903 --> 15:04.905
And you cut around the perimeter.

15:17.918 --> 15:21.421
And there you have it,
ladies and gentlemen,

15:21.504 --> 15:23.798
the human brain.

15:23.924 --> 15:26.593
Once the brain stem
of an individual,

15:26.676 --> 15:29.679
I'm talking about the reticular
activating system,

15:29.763 --> 15:32.307
heart regulation,
respiratory center.

15:32.390 --> 15:34.851
Once these activities cease,

15:34.935 --> 15:40.231
the brain can only survive
an additional six to 12 minutes.

15:40.315 --> 15:43.193
Six to 12 minutes.

15:45.278 --> 15:48.239
Until...

15:48.323 --> 15:52.869
brain death brings about
an irreversible conclusion.

16:01.544 --> 16:05.548
